CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 6, 1952, pg. 14, reads: "Prepare for 'Hanging of Greens' - The committee in charge of making plans for the annual 'Hanging of the Greens' celebration at the Centre Avenue YWCA met last week. The affair will be held on Dec. 6 and 7.  Left to right: Ruth B. Gwyn, co-chairman; Dorothy Graves, Alyce H. Parr, chairman; Lois Thompson, adult director, and Elmira Higgins, secretary.  Others not in picture, but on the committee, are Anita Mike, LaVenta McKinney, Merelese Angell and Mamie B. Steward. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Ruth B. Gwyn, Dorothy Graves, Alyce H. Parr, Lois Thompson, and Elmira Higgins, posed in Centre Avenue YWCA
